 <text>
  <front>
   <head>The POWER of BEAUTY.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">O GODDESS of eternal Smiles,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Bright  the fair,</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Who taught  pleasing Wiles,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">By which she won</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">the witty and the vain,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Who laugh'd at Beauty's Pow'r;</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">But now the conquer'd humble Swain</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Adores a painted Flow'r.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">With  Art my Song inspire,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Whose Lips of rosy Hue</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Can ne'er the partial Audience tire,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Tho' wiser  do.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="4" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Tho'  Wit and Sense refin'd,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Flows easy from her Tongue;</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Her Soul but coarsly is enshrin'd,</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">So  in the wrong.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="5" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="17" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Hark,  speaks â€” that blooming Fair,</l>
     <l n="18" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">See Crowds are gathering round</l>
     <l n="19" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">With open Mouths: and wildly stare</l>
     <l n="20" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">To catch the empty Sound.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="6" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="21" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">See  with a Judgment clear,</l>
     <l n="22" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">With manly Wisdom blest;</l>
     <l n="23" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Wit, Learning, Prudence, all appear</l>
     <l n="24" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">In that unruffled Breast.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="7" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="25" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">But yet no Beau for  dies,</l>
     <l n="26" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">No Sonnets pave her way;</l>
     <l n="27" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Say, Muse, from whence these Evils rise,</l>
     <l n="28" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Why  Teeth decay.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="8" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="29" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Then, why do rev'rend Sages rail</l>
     <l n="30" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">At Woman's wanton Pride?</l>
     <l n="31" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">If Wisdom, Wit, and Prudence fail,</l>
     <l n="32" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Let meaner Arts be try'd.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="9" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="33" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Those Arts to please are only meant;</l>
     <l n="34" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">But with an angry Frown,</l>
     <l n="35" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The Queen of Wisdom lately sent</l>
     <l n="36" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">This Proclamation down:</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="10" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="37" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">with the azure Eyes,</l>
     <l n="38" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And thus the Statute runs,</l>
     <l n="39" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">If you wou'd have your Daughters wise,</l>
     <l n="40" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Take care to mend your Sons.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
